docs.abstract: The chief executive of SoftBank, Masayoshi Son, and his ambitious Vision Fund, are deeply enmeshed with the oil-rich kingdom, which has promised to invest $45 billion.
docs.snippet: The chief executive of SoftBank, Masayoshi Son, and his ambitious Vision Fund, are deeply enmeshed with the oil-rich kingdom, which has promised to invest $45 billion.
docs.lead_paragraph: Since the disappearance and apparent killing of a dissident journalist in a Saudi Arabian consulate, some of the most powerful figures in business are distancing themselves from the kingdom. There is one prominent exception: Masayoshi Son, chief executive of the SoftBank Group.

headline.main: Powerful Executives Have Stepped Away From the Saudis. Not SoftBank’s.
headline.print_headline: Saudi Links Leave Chief Of SoftBank In Tight Spot

byline.original: By Kate Kelly, Landon Thomas Jr., Andrew Ross Sorkin and Erin Griffith

docs.abstract: Known as a mega-round in Silicon Valley, large-scale fund raising is producing a frenzy around tech companies with enough reach and momentum to absorb a large check.
docs.snippet: Known as a mega-round in Silicon Valley, large-scale fund raising is producing a frenzy around tech companies with enough reach and momentum to absorb a large check.
docs.lead_paragraph: In late April, when Mike Massaro set out to get $40 million to $75 million in funding for his payments start-up, Flywire, he contacted a small group of investors he already knew. But word quickly got around, and other investors flooded his inbox with $200 million of investment offers, half of which he turned down.

headline.main: $100 Million Was Once Big Money for a Start-Up. Now, It’s Common.
headline.print_headline: For Start-Up Investors,  The Sky’s the Limit

docs.abstract: The fitness company selling stationary bikes and subscriptions to live classes once confused investors. Now, after new financing of $550 million, it’s the toast of Silicon Valley.
docs.snippet: The fitness company selling stationary bikes and subscriptions to live classes once confused investors. Now, after new financing of $550 million, it’s the toast of Silicon Valley.
docs.lead_paragraph: For Peloton’s first two years in business, venture capital investors didn’t get it. The company’s founders struggled to convince them that blending stationary bikes and streaming live video classes would work. It had to cobble together money from a network of more than 200 angel investors to get off the ground.

headline.main: Peloton’s New Infusion Made It a $4 Billion Company in 6 Years
headline.print_headline: Fitness Firm, Going Strong, Reaches $4 Billion Mark

docs.abstract: The Federal Reserve gave clean bills of health to top banks, but told Goldman Sachs and Morgan Stanley to freeze shareholder payouts at last year’s levels.
docs.snippet: The Federal Reserve gave clean bills of health to top banks, but told Goldman Sachs and Morgan Stanley to freeze shareholder payouts at last year’s levels.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Federal Reserve on Thursday gave clean bills of health to most of the largest American banks, allowing them to return money to shareholders, but it forced Goldman Sachs and Morgan Stanley to freeze such payouts around last year’s levels.

headline.main: Bank ‘Stress Tests’ Results Clear Way for Wall Street to Reward Investors
headline.print_headline: Fed Clears the Way for Banks To Reward Their Shareholders

docs.abstract: A senior banker called Goldman Sachs’s whistle-blower hotline, a rare dissent by a partner at the firm. His superiors, including the next chief executive, told him to relax.

docs.abstract: A meeting in May was meant for a discussion of foreign meddling in this year’s midterm elections. But some tech officials left frustrated.
docs.snippet: A meeting in May was meant for a discussion of foreign meddling in this year’s midterm elections. But some tech officials left frustrated.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Eight of the tech industry’s most influential companies, in anticipation of a repeat of the Russian meddling that occurred during the 2016 presidential campaign, met with United States intelligence officials last month to discuss preparations for this year’s midterm elections.

headline.main: Top Tech Companies Met With Intelligence Officials to Discuss Midterms
headline.print_headline: To Deter Midterm Meddling, U.S. Met With Tech Giants
